Female . COLORATION, SURFACE AND VESTITURE: As in male; thoracic pleura and abdomen brighter than in male, of same color with dorsum. STRUCTURE: Very similar to male in all respects, insignificantly more ovoid, total length 3.0– 3.2 , body 2.7–2.8 × as long as basal width of pronotum. Head: vertex wider than in male (
Fig. 11
), 1.9–2.1 × as wide as dorsal width one eye; antennal segment II 0.6 × as long as basal width of pronotum, equal in length to width of head, distinctly thinner than segment I, slightly incrassate at extreme apex. Thorax: Pronotum 2.1–2.3 × as wide as long, 1.5–1.6 × as wide as head.

Distribution. The species is known from Spain , southern France , Corsica , and Sicily (
Wagner 1975
;
Carapezza 1988
;
Coffin & Moulet 1989
).
